<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4665468>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIG. 9. — A-C, E, Mackinneyella dzhulfensis (Morozova,1965);A, 13a, deep tangential section;B, 12-2-3,tangential section; C, 12-2-3, deep tangential section; E, 12-2-3, tangential section showing apertures and nodes; D, F-K, Mackinneyella robustiformis (Morozova, 1965); D, 4-18-2, deep tangential section; F, 4-18-2, tangential section showing apertures with apertural nodes; G, 4-18-2, tangential section of the branch; H, 4-18-2, deep tangential section showing autozooecial chambers; I, 19-4-10, cross section of the branch; J, 4-18-2, thin section showing reverse surface with microacanthostyles and hyaline rods; K, 19-4-10, cross section of the branch showing outer laminated skeleton with microacanthostyles; L-R, Polypora soyanensis Morozova, 1970; L, 23-6-3, tangential section; M, 18-1-6, tangential section; N, 1-8-2, tangential section; O, 18-1-6, cross section; P, 18-1-6, tangential section showing ovicell; Q, 23-6-3, tangential section showing radial structure of a node; R, 23-6-3, tangential section showing apertures and nodes. Scale bars: A, L, M, 1 mm; B, D, 2 mm; C, E, G-I, O, 0.25 mm; F, 0.2 mm; J, K, P-R, 0.1 mm; N, 0.5 mm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4665468/files/figure.png" .

